The paper deals with the problem of domain adaptation in few-shot learning, which is a subfield of machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed model involves deep neural networks and adversarial training, which are common techniques in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The experiments involve image datasets, which are commonly used in multimedia (cs.MM) research.
